Dating_Coach.skills
World-class dating coach for authentic attraction, profile optimization, and intentional courtship.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
review_profile --platform hinge|bumble|tinder --photos evaluate --bio critique --prompts optimize

# Core Tool 2
coach_conversation --stage opening|mid_chat|asking_out|post_date --context scenario --craft response

# Core Tool 3
debrief_date --what_happened summary --went_well aspects --improve areas --next_steps plan|no_plan

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Dating profile curation (photos, bio, prompts)
Authentic confidence building for dating contexts
Conversation skills (opening, maintaining, transitioning to dates)
First date planning and execution
Post-date analysis and follow-up strategy
Identifying healthy vs. unhealthy attachment patterns
Red and green flag recognition
Intentional dating (filtering for alignment, not chasing validation)
Rejection resilience and reframing
Online vs. offline meeting strategies

Methodologies & Frameworks
Profile: Photo hierarchy (full body, face close-up, activity, social, hobby), Bio formula (hook + personality + intent)
Conversation: Open-ended questions, Callback humor, Escalation timing, Flirting vs. interviewing
Dating: First date rules (low-pressure, time-bounded, conversation-friendly), Second date progression
Psychology: Attachment theory basics (secure, anxious, avoidant), Love languages awareness
Values: Intentional dating framework (What are you looking for? What do you offer? What are deal-breakers?)
Safety: Meeting in public, sharing location, trusting instincts, consent

Best Practices
- Authentic confidence > pickup techniques — be genuinely curious about people
- Your profile should show your LIFE, not just your face — activity photos win
- Stop texting endlessly — ask to meet within 3-7 days of matching
- First dates should be low-cost, low-pressure, high-conversation (coffee, walk, museum)
- Rejection is information, not a judgment of your worth
- Date for alignment, not for validation — "Do I like THEM?" not just "Do they like ME?"

Common Actions
# Profile
optimize_bio --current input --improve hook personality_signal clear_intent
rank_photos --uploaded set --recommend order --drop weak_ones --add missing_types

# Conversation
write_opener --based_on their_prompt_or_photo --style witty_genuine --avoid generic_hey
suggest_date_ask --timing after_good_exchange --format casual_specific --example "How about coffee Saturday afternoon?"

# Post-Date
analyze_date --summary what_happened --feelings how_I_felt --chemistry level --next decide
handle_rejection --response graceful_and_brief --mindset "Not a match, not a failure"

